content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were sitting on lawn chairs in our back yard smoking cigarettes. we recently moved to this house in a rural area outside of corvallis so on clear nights the star gazing is pretty awesome. i looked up and saw an incredibly bright star-like object moving pretty fast directly overhead. it was as bright as polaris is out here on clear nights. i pointed it out to my wife and it began to slow down. my wife took no intrest in it and went back inside. it continued on a straight-line path at a much slower speed. at this point i pulled out my phone to take a video of the object, but my phone camera was having a hard time picking up the image. i stood up and walked further out in the yard and zoomed in, hoping it would be visible. while i was looking at my phone trying to get a good shot of the object, i could not see it. when i looked at the sky again it was gone.

i feel like i should mention that i saw a ufo when we were living in corvallis about six months ago. ever since that day i have always been watching the sky. there had been a recent increase in air traffic in this area, so i have seen many planes and know what they look like. i have also seen many satellites and i have never seen one this bright. my wife thinks it was just a satellite and thinks i have an "overactive imagination" although she has never said it to me. i know she doesn't believe me, but i understand. if i didn't watch the night sky as often as i do, i probably would have thought it was a bright satellite. but i have never seen a satellite that bright or change speed before. 

the video footage i took is pretty useless, but i attached it anyway.
content.summary: Starlite object as bright as polaris moving fast then slowing down. traveling in a straight path

content.detailedDescription: Watching laser lights from near by festival from roof window felt something fly overhead watched a very large craft with three white lights fly across the sky extremely fast and silent waited for a noise as thought maybe three planes flying together but silent it disappeared into the night
content.summary: Huge silent craft flew over very large very very fast

content.detailedDescription: Just got in my above ground pool, looked around to see the clouds above. i looked to the west, above my 6 foot fence. i saw; what at first glance was a mylar balloon ascending from about a quarter mile away. it had the speed or motion of  ball released under water. it then leveled out and came east; toward me. it moved fairly quickly slightly north of me. davis monthan air force base is about 3/4 of a mile directly south and i would liken the speed of the object like that of an a10 going by, only lower and no sound. it started to sparkle more or flicker raising in altitude as it continued east. as it got further east and higher in the sky i noticed that it was not as high as the cloud cover. it then seemed to stop and remain stationary for 4-5 seconds. at this point i would guess it to be about 3-5 miles away and the only reason i could still make it out at all was from the continuous flickering or random reflecting it was producing. the mylar balloon theory was crushed after it leveled out and started coming my direction when it was to the west. when it was as close as it got to me, i would guess the size to be at least ten times larger than an average balloon but smaller than a car. finally, as the object continued to move; after the short stationary pause, it seemed to go into the cloud. i figured that would be the last i saw it but about 10 or 15 seconds later i saw it again what seemed to be twice as far away. 7-10 miles only noticeable because of the flashing. it then continued away till i got hot and dunked under the water.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Flickering light ascended straight up then came easterly smooth but quick.

content.detailedDescription:
I was out filming in my yard with an old camera. i was watching a bunny then i started to look around in the sky (1st look) and saw nothing. i resumed looking around my yard then i looked at the mountains, then scrolled towards 2 cottonwood trees. in the center, i glanced around.

it was until i reviewed the tape that i saw it:
hovering near a cloud, it was a near-transparent pyramid with only the outline visible. in less than a second, it quickly went up and 'cloaked' itself. i was pretty spooked... and i showed it to my parents and they said it could be a reflection or a cloaked ship.
content.summary: Hovering, pyramid like object below cloud line, transparent

content.detailedDescription: Sometime in sept 2001 was on the coney island boardwalk around w31st sitting on a bench with my girlfriend who was pregnant at the time. we saw a flash of light in the sky and all of sudden the sand on the beach rolled up like a wave and then some craft all black was above us. we made an attempt to run but then there was a bright light, we couldn't move in my peripheral vision i can see ppl walking past us and my gf was looking up with tears in her eyes and then a humanoid figure surrounded by or was in the form of a bright light appeared and stepped up behind her and vanished then all was normal again, we took off running until we go to the w31st and there was something above the clouds i estimated to be larger than central park with 3/4 rows of light rotating clock/counter clockwise and we saw 13 smaller crafts cone from the larger one heading in separate directions then there was something that looked like a cloud shaped like a ruler with definition, 7 black crafts in the same shape came out of it and then the sky turned all sorts of colors and the clouds rolled in an undescribable way. on the 15th of sept 2001 my son was born and on the heel of his left foot there's a dark make very defined that looks like a ufo or pyramid. i honestly don't care if this is taken as a joke. just thought i'd share
content.summary: Sand rolled up like waves, bright light, can't move, humanoid figure in the form of bright entered someone

content.detailedDescription: My father and i were laying down on the bench at our patio, it was very light drizzle and overcast skies. my father told me to look towards right below the clouds and i saw one light moving from side to side, seemed to be very far, approx 10 km or more away, then another light arrived from the clouds. i asked my dad "what are those things?" he replied "ufos" , i asked "like extraterrestrial?" he said "yes. no human craft known can flight at such speed.Nothing covers a distance of 5kms in less than a second. keep watching." the lights seemed to go towards each other, as if playing "tag" for around 3 minutes, then suddenly flew diagonally towards the sky. no fear, just a sense of curiosity and wonder. i don't believe in ets, but that was too much to ignore.
content.summary: 2 ufos flying from side to side, against each other's directions then flew away diagonally

content.detailedDescription: I was at my friends birthday party in a little village that hasn't so many street lights it was already very dark. we went outside and played hide and seek. me and 2 other friends were hiding in a very dark place between 2 trashcans. i looked into the sky and at the stars, then there were 3 big lights in a triangle shape and a little red light in the middle. it was moving very fast and the lights were'nt flashing like airplane lights are, they were just shining continuous. it made no sounds although it was very big and near to me. it was flying in a straight line and dissapeared behind some houses after a couple seconds. when i first saw it i thought it was an airplane but like i've said the lights were'nt flashing and also there was'nt a airport anywhere near by so why should a plane this size fly so close to the ground and make no sounds. when i saw the object i felt really weird and couldn't really talk but after it was gone i asked my two friends if they've seen it too, they had but they thought it was just an airplane and they said i am mad for thinking it was an ufo. also they did'nt really listened when i tried to explain why i thought it ws an ufo. i am still really confused what this was.
content.summary: Triangle shaped fast, big soundless object with 3 big white and 1 small red lamp.

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting back enjoying life on the beach. yes i had a four beers and listening to my music. as i looked up just in time to see a beige colored, wing shape object soar through the air overhead. it was higher than the building to my south as it flew over it. the span of it side to side was about 3/4 the width building. it flew maybe 20 ft higher than the building. i only see it for about 3, 4 secs. first thought was it's a bird but at 230am? i saw no wings flap. approximately 1hr before this i saw a shooting star far off to the southeast and high in the sky. most likely just a coincidence.

content.detailedDescription:
So, this day, i smoking cigarettes outside. i'm used to do it looking at the stars. i have a certain knowledge of the normal position of the star and the planets and always look for venus or orion's belt, and normaly, i know before looking for it more or less where it should be.

this particular night when i look first glance at the sky, i see venus out of ambitual site. when i try to look venus where it should be, he certainly was there. so it was not venus. when a come back to see this object, i realize the object is moving, so a belief to be a satellite or the iss.

i keep track of the object and realize is not moving in linear and  change the inicial nw to sw derection to w. when i start to trying figured out what it is, the object make a total stoppage and stay like a minute in the same spot. 

i began to feel afraid, because there is not anything that can go to that height  suddenly  stop . after that 1 min,  stoped in the same spot, the object become brighter and disappear.

object it always the same size, and same bright of venus. only in the end become brighter and orange like color before disappear. in addition to this, it's important mention the " serra da estrela" ( the most elevated place in mainland portugal ) it's right behind me, and the object appear to come moving from there.

i stay with the feeling that the object stopped and disappeared, somehow realize i was watching it. i am very sceptical, and a never share this with no one, but haunts me down not know what i see that night. ( sorry my lousy english)

content.detailedDescription: Me and some of my family members were sitting in our backyard at about 10:30 pm. we were just having fun/talking when i looked up and asked "is that a shooting star"? because the object was moving and looked like a star! it stopped mid flight very quickly for about 3 seconds (where my sister pointed out that it looked like a diamond) then turned very slightly and kept moving at a high rate of speed. we managed to see this again about 30 seconds later once it passed over our large tree, and it appeared that it was way higher in the air, then all of a sudden it seemed that it got so high we couldn't see it anymore.
content.summary: Me, and about 5 family members were sitting in our back patio when we saw a "starlike" object in the sky moving at high speed after stopping very briefly mid-flight

content.detailedDescription:
June 9, 2016 (data recorded at 11:36 p.M.)

my life partner and i set out tonight to consciously look for ufos and to stargaze as we often do. sedona is a dark sky city as well as one of the e.T. capitols of the world, so we often engage in long, late night drives in this place. we began our drive around 9:25 p.M. and did a loop of the village, went to west sedona, and then came back to the area in between the main part of sedona and the village (near the chapel of the holy cross). we drove here for well over an hour. we saw several small ufos which may have been shooting stars… the high number of them that we saw made it likely that a few were e.T. aircraft but i have no solid proof for this other than my own personal feelings. after we engaged in this behavior, we headed towards the village on 89a. we were the only ones on the road for several miles and we were in between cathedral rock and bell rock. i could see cathedral rock’s shadowy outline out of the corner of my right eye slightly behind us. my partner (the driver of our car) spotted a very bright light off in the distance in the sky. from our vantage point it seemed to be hovering over the cliff walls to the right of bell rock (to the right when heading towards the village). it also appeared to be 2-3 miles away.   it was brighter than sirius and venus combined together and it just sat there motionless. it was impossible to immediately tell exactly how high it was but it was definitely far too low for an ordinary plane. my partner stopped the car in the middle of 89a (there was no one else around) and we stared at it… trying to discern whether it was a man-made craft or not. i began to get the feeling that it was not. it was definitely not a helicopter (no noise and it did not behave at all like a helicopter). i decided to go out on a limb and i yelled out the window (we had the windows and sunroof down), “i see you family!” (this was in reference to extraterrestrials who i consider to be my “star family.”) the instant i said that, the white light became so bright that i had to look away for a moment because it hurt my eyes… it was almost like whoever was inside the craft hit a switch that turned the craft lights on to full power. the white light appeared to be emanating from a dome shaped structure on the top of the craft. when i looked back a split second later, the craft was rapidly descending and heading straight for our car at astonishing speed. it reached us in about 3 seconds. chris scooted the car forward a few feet since a tree was starting to get in the way (the breeze blew the branches into my line of sight). the craft sped so quickly to us that it was almost scary. it was completely silent and flew at a very low altitude. it was pretty large and definitely not a drone. it was shaped almost like an upside down “y” and had a definite triangular presence to it and we saw blinking lights in the corners of the “wings” as it literally came to a point right above our car. the craft slowed down above our car. it didn’t stop but it came at us with the seeming intention of letting us know that its passengers saw us. it started to curve over us a little bit almost like it was going to head towards airport mesa behind us. i turned to my partner to see their face (full of pure awe) and when i turned around to see where the craft went, it was completely gone. no man made craft can move that quickly and we had clear visibility from every direction for many miles. even if the craft had shut off all of the lights, we would have still been able to see the outline due to a bit of backlighting from the uptown/west sedona area (it is a dark sky city but if you are headed in the direction of the shopping/tourist areas there is a bit of light pollution). the craft was completely silent the entire time. my partner stated that if we had hit a baseball hard enough, we probably could have hit it. if it had flown towards cathedral rock it would have crashed into it because of how low it was. the fact that it shined its light as brightly as it could the minute i addressed it and the fact that it literally zoomed to our car like a little white fireball was extremely intriguing. my partner remembers a blue light, white light, and green light. i saw the massive white light and the green light, but instead of blue i saw a couple of red lights blinking. this may have been because my own vantage point was slightly different. my partner resumed driving because there was no point in just sitting there and when i looked at the car clock it said 11:11 p.M. on the dot which we found to be very synchronous. everything was seen with our naked eyes. i had my partner draw a model of the craft we saw (very quickly) when we got home while the image was fresh. when we got home i instantly raced to the internet to look up triangle shaped craft… apparently it is one of the most common craft-types seen here in sedona and some people have reported seeing e.T.S shortly after these types of sightings. there was a report made last year (much like what i have described) here in sedona. the interesting thing is that it takes almost the exact path that ours did (except backwards… from airport mesa direction towards cathedral) and is very close to the same location where our sighting occurred. that particular sighting also had several witnesses. something very interesting to note is that the ufo sighting in that report that had several witnesses also occurred in june last year… around 10 p.M.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Ufo reached us in 3 seconds from miles away. responded to our words by turning bright lights on and coming to us.

content.detailedDescription: I live in the yakima valley and saw this bright as the moon orb from the west. west of where i'm at is mt. adams. it swooped into the valley and got really bright, then swooped out and got dimmer. as it was leaving a plane from the prosser airport could be seen ascending and moving in a northwest direction. approximate time as 10pm, or 1015pm, as i was taking my dog out. the orb continued into the southeast, towards oregon or idaho. it was big, then got dim and disappeared. my mother, my sister, and i saw it. i saw the whole thing, they saw it depart and disappear.
content.summary: Orb moving from mt. adams area into oregon or idaho. viewed from yakima valley around 10pm pacific time.

content.detailedDescription:

when i got home i looked at the video but the object appeared to be white not a glowing amber and without the tail. still unsure what it was. think i'll stay in the rest of the night.
by the way, the video is still on my phone. tried downloading it to my computer, every photo and video downloaded fine except this video. weird.

content.detailedDescription:
At 10:03 pm 2016 in rural nw  oregon, my husband and i had stepped onto our back deck to enjoy the stars.

content.detailedDescription: I was at my home on my front lawn talking on the phone to my father. the sky is completely clear tonight and i was just looking up into the sky while walking around and talking to him. i have the exact time of when i received a call from my dad so i included that in the report. anyways i first observed what i think was a passenger plane traveling north east from my city. i heard the noise of a jet engine so i looked up. it had a white light towards the nose and flashing lights underneath. nothing uncommon, but after watching the plane while talking on the phone for a couple more seconds i thought i saw what looked like a satellite trailing behind it pretty close. i thought it was a satellite at first but it became brighter than the airplane so i thought this can't be a satellite it was too bright. it was a complete white ball of light is what i can best describe it as. but the light was brighter than the white light on the airplane. after watching it for a while trying to figure if it was satellite i observed it slow down and create distance between itself and plane for maybe 30 seconds. what was the strangest was after the airplane was out of sight i saw this light look like it stood in place and then became dimmer and dimmer smaller than the stars behind it and just completely faded away. i don't know if it was a jet behind the plan but i only heard the engine of the passenger plane and there was no sonic boom or any other noise.
content.summary: Uknown object trailing what appeared to be a passenger plane then take of toward space and disapeared.

content.detailedDescription:
I went outside; i didn't really need to for anything but i just thought it might be nice to walk a bit. i kept asking myself why was i bothering to go out. lol. i remember coming back towards my apartment and saw this huge orange globe over the tree line which isn't really that high up; i thought it might actually come towards me, but then it changed direction i was surprised by how close it got. when i first saw it i thought maybe it was one of those chinese lanterns or a balloon of some kind but it seemed to transparent and too bright and solid looking. something about it wasn't indicative of a balloon. it almost appeared intelligent or curious in some way. it hovered and then it made a flawless climb up way past the clouds and disappeared. i just remember being very impressed by its brilliance. it was very beautiful and bright.
i felt a little sad as it left; i wished i could have had more time to look at it.
content.summary: Orange orb -- very bright and pulsating. amazingly brilliant in color.

content.detailedDescription:
in october, 1984, i and my wife and two other couples were camping in the mountains about 20 miles above carson, washington at the start of deer hunting season. a little after dark, i and my two hunting buddies  decided to take a powerful spotlight and drive up to an area a couple of miles from our camp to scope out a clearing by the road where we had seen several deer beds in the area that day, to decide if we wanted go on a stand there early the next morning.
  this road was fairly high up in the hills and, because of the direction we parked, faced west down the columbia river towards troutdale and the portland airport, both of which we could see clearly. we hadn't had anything to drink or that could impair our senses or powers of observation.
  one of my friends, who was seated in the middle of the front seat between myself and our other friend and was therefore unable to see the clearing, was watching the lights of troutdale and the portland airport and the lights of airplanes as they landed and departed.
  suddenly he exclaimed loudly "what the heck was that" and punched me and our other friend in the arm to get our attention. when we asked him what he had seen, he said "just watch the lights in the sky down by the airport".
  as we all watched the lights, one of them  suddenly, instantaneously, jumped to the right, a distance that we all agreed was about one to two miles. it remained in that position for a short time, a minute or two, then suddenly jumped straight up about the same distance, remained at that height for a short time, then suddenly jumped downward about the same distance. these maneuvers continued for several minutes, each time leaving a brief streak on the retinas of our eyes . i and my friends all saw these maneuvers at the same time, exclaiming "oh" or "what the heck" at the same time. we could also tell the light was moving towards us. it eventually passed over a hilltop to our left at a height of about 400 to 500 feet above our position. as it passed over, we heard a sort of hum-buzz sound, unlike any airplane or helicopter we had ever heard. the light it emitted was a strong, white, non-directional glow, not a beam. we never saw the shape or size of the craft itself, just the bright glow of the light it emitted.
  a few years later, about 1991, i happened to overhear a fellow employee talking to another employee about an experience he had one night while he was working working aboard a fishing boat in the gulf of alaska. as he described this experience, i realized he was describing, almost word for word, exactly the same thing my friends and i had witnessed in the mountains above carson washington in 1984.
content.summary: Saw light in sky several miles away, making impossibly fast position changes over fairly large distances.

content.detailedDescription: On wednesday night june 8th around 9 pm i was alone fishing for catfish in the family lake .Low on the western horizon the only way i know how to describe it,is a bright round object brilliant silver white in color just appeared then (telported) from its stationary position towards the south. i say teleported because it appeared and reappeared three times covering the whole western sky in a matter of seconds .On the next night june the 9th thursday night me and a friend are in the same location fishing around 9pm i witnessed  a round object identical to the night before but it appeared then disaperd very fast two times in about a 20 minute span .I screamed at my friend to look both times but he didn't see it.Around 9:45 the light came back on same spot in the sky then another light appeared to its right same shape and color ,then a few seconds later the first object on the left went out but in a split second came back on but this time the lights were dark orange rectangle shape from right to left came on one at a time till there was 5 then i could actually see a shape of a disc shaped object.Then both objects disappeared then in a instant we seen two reddish orange orbs speeding off to the north one was moving in a straight line the other seemed to circle the other, once it made a complete 360 they both spiraled each other then went out fast as they appeared .This all took place in under two minutes ,i came back for a third night but seen nothing. i know my aircraft civilian and military very well also the stars and planets what i seen has rocked me to the core of everything i know and was not restricted by gravity are laws of physics  the speed at witch they moved is beyond any thing iv ever seen.
content.summary: Life changing

content.detailedDescription:
June 11,2016 7:06 pm, still light out. 
rohnert park in my back yard gardening. my back hurt so i stood up to stretch while looking up and to the east over the park i live in.  it was cigar like but had two parts. like two long balloons tied together. moving straight and fast enough this old lady had to trot 10 feet in few seconds to keep seeing it. it went behind the tall redwood tree in front of my house. i trotted back west on my property to see it come from behind the tree but it never did!  i went up on top of my porch to see it, but it was gone. like it disappeared! 
i thought what did i just see?  2 cigar shaped balloons tied together with a larger part in the back on top of it.  then it hit me... it had no wings!!  how could it be a plane then!! i realized it had to have been a ufo!!  then my heart started beating faster as i ran in the house and text my daughter and told her. i also said i was reporting it to mufon!! ( she thinks i'm nuts). i have seen others as far back as 1971-72 in sacramento ca. 
i'm 62 so she thinks i'm just crazier in my years. boy is she wrong!!
i'm reporting it now in my house.    report 7:40 pm 6-11-2016


ps.  i felt nervous and anxious inside so i went out to plant flowers again. i spotted it about 10 minutes of planting, up in the air.
content.summary: Above my house going south rapidly. went behind a redwood tree and did not come out. disappeared!

content.detailedDescription: Well was just taking random pictures. then the next day i was looking through them and notice what i had caught on camera. i just found this sight to report it and send pictures i have taken. i always see them in east texas.
content.summary: Was snapping random pictures and notice i had caught ufos in the sky.

content.detailedDescription: I deliver newspapers every morning. while traveling south on grant street in shamokin, pa. a flash/twinkle/movement of light caught the corner of my eye as i had just tossed a paper onto the porch of an educational building. i looked up into the perfectly clear dawn sky and saw the two cigar-shaped items. my jaw dropped and then i fumbled for my cell phone and its camera. i got pictures but they aren't great. i strained to hear anything thinking it might be a jet or of something of that sort. way too low for two jets. no wings. no discernible human air-flight apparatus features of any sort. they were headed two different directions away from each other. no contrails. not beacon lights flashing. in two of my pictures the items appear white. in the other pictures they are black dots. i see jets taking off and flying all the time on this route. they are way much higher than these were. i like the quiet of the early morning. i know this route cold - i notice things when they aren't normally there. i said to my husband about it and showed him the pictures. i haven't touched the picks or nothing. i need somebody to see my pictures. they are from my phone and not of the best quality. i will attempt to upload them for you but it may be difficult to see. i apologize for the lousy quality of the pictures. please contact me if you have any questions or wish to talk about it. thank you for your time and attention to this sighting. (not the first time i've seen them. just the first time i've had enough "this here" to report it.
content.summary: Saw two ufo's. no sound. no contrails. no tracking lights. bright silver. cigar shaped. took pictures
